{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XNe4CPf9jxsSrSfVu9oLQZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the problem now. The Elasticsearch configmap has `discovery.seed_hosts` but is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. This is the bootstrap problem. In Elasticsearch 7.x, you need `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to bootstrap a brand new cluster. Without it, nodes can't elect a master.\n\nThe configmap is missing:\n```yaml\ncluster.initial_master_nodes:\n  - es-cluster-0\n  - es-cluster-1\n  - es-cluster-2\n```\n\nThe fix:\nI need to add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the configmap to let the cluster bootstrap, then remove it once the cluster is healthy since it's only needed for initial formation. Let me check how the config is mounted in the statefulset to understand the full picture.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1515,"cache_read_input_tokens":29736,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1515},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7d514ccf-2622-43f2-ab4c-cf46be3a9710","uuid":"6f9ef50a-018f-46cf-a5dc-6886b261533a","request_id":"req_011CccEtZJyRr7Af1jwpskgs"}
