{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WWDoVWaqV2w9wQf33t5q9W","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the logs go up to the point where ES is trying to bootstrap. The last log entry shows it's in `BootstrapChecks`. It's trying to form a cluster, but it can't because `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is not set.\n\nThe ES 7.x docs say: when a cluster is started for the first time, `cluster.initial_master_nodes` must be set. Without it, ES won't be able to bootstrap the cluster.\n\nThe fix is clear:\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the configmap\n2. Restart all pods simultaneously (they haven't formed a cluster yet, and PVCs are fresh)\n3. Wait for the cluster to form\n4. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the configmap\n5. Do a rolling restart\n\nSince the PVCs are only 31 seconds old and the cluster never formed, there's no existing cluster state to worry about. There's an interesting tension here though—the StatefulSet uses `Parallel` pod management, which creates all pods at once, but the update strategy is `RollingUpdate`, which applies changes sequentially. For the initial restart to pick up the new configmap, I'll need to delete all pods manually so they get recreated immediately.\n\nAfter that, I'll use the kubectl rollout restart command to perform a proper rolling update once the bootstrap settings are removed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2180,"cache_read_input_tokens":36824,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2180},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7d514ccf-2622-43f2-ab4c-cf46be3a9710","uuid":"e0aaa3db-574e-4499-8561-196afac3bd8e","request_id":"req_011CccExwnCNjgjYE4prJ5iv"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WWDoVWaqV2w9wQf33t5q9W","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is stalled at `BootstrapChecks` — the configmap is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, which ES 7.x requires to bootstrap a new cluster. Here's the fix plan:\n\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the configmap\n2. Restart all pods simultaneously (fresh PVCs, no existing cluster state)\n3. Wait for cluster to form\n4. Remove the bootstrap-only setting from the configmap\n5. Rolling restart to flush the setting from all running nodes\n\n**Step 1: Patch the configmap to add `cluster.initial_master_nodes`**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2180,"cache_read_input_tokens":36824,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2180},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7d514ccf-2622-43f2-ab4c-cf46be3a9710","uuid":"0e2e636d-eb42-44dd-82d8-5328dc1a5f31","request_id":"req_011CccExwnCNjgjYE4prJ5iv"}
